text: The Lahore High Court is based in Lahore, Punjab, Pakistan. It was established as a high court on 1 March 1882. The Lahore High Court has jurisdiction over Punjab. The High Court's main seat is in Lahore, but there are benches in three other Pakistani cities: Rawalpindi, Multan and Bahawalpur. ==References== Category:Lahore Category:1919 establishments in Asia Category:20th-century establishments in Pakistan Category:Pakistani courts
